{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_irma_ver01/data/sn88078614/00516994071/1949012801/0923.xml":{"full_text":"LEARN TO DANCE THE EASY WAY\nBeginner\u2019s\u2014Advance Young or Old!\nLEARN THE WALTZ, FOX TROT,\nJITTERBUG, RHUMBA, POLKA, Etc.\nChildren, 3 years and up, learn Tap, Toe,\nBallet, Acrobatics, Etc.\nNew Enrollments Accepted This Week\nRATES WITHIN THE REACH OF ALL\nWrite MADISON SCHOOL, DREAM-HAVEN, Chapel Rd., R.\nF. D. 3, Madison, Ohio, or Phone Sundays Madison 2488\n9 a. m. to 9 p. m.\nGOOD,HOME-MADEWINES\nf\nWe Know\nOur Wines\nare good\n\u2019cause we\nmake our\nown.\nCelebrate\nThe\nOccasion\nwith Our\nFINE\nWINES\nKAPEL WINERY\n440 Courtland Street\nFairport\nYOULL APPRECIATE THESE\nat\nTANTRE\u2019S MARKET\n440 Fifth St.\nPhone 4821\nFairport\nThere\u2019s Plenty Here For Everyone!\n\nArmour\u2019s Cloverbloom\nBUTTER\n1b. 68c\nPORK STEAK, lean\n1b. 49c\nShort Ribs of Beef\n1b. 35c\nAssorted Cold Cuts\n100%> Pure\nGROUND BEEF\nLean Sliced Bacon\nlb. 49c\n1b. 49c\n1b. 59c\n4\nBacon Squares 1b. 33c\nPillsbury\u2019s or Ceresota\nFlour\n24%-lb.\nBag\n$1.98\nManhattan\nSOAP CHIPS\n5-lb. box 69c\nSlants and Comments\nby Kenneth Babbs\nA Bright Future Ahead?\nA\nprominent newspaperman\nhad just concluded an optimistic\ntalk in which he predicted con\ntinued and greater prosperity,\nindustrial expansion and scienti\nfic and political advances for ma\nny years to come in the United\nStates.\nThen the inevitable question\nwas posed by a bright young at\ntorney and Lake county official.\n\u201cWon\u2019t business be frightened\nby government inhibitions, with\ncurtailment and depression the\nresult?\u201d\nThe newspaper editor answer\ned that many business leaders\nwith whom he had talked were\nplanning or were in the actual\nprocess of expanding and devel\noping or producing many new\nproducts, and so obviously were\nnot frightened.\nAlthough one shouldn\u2019t be, I\nam continually surprised by the\nnaivete of inteligent local busi\nness and civic leaders who can\nnever seem to believe that the\nworld does move and life and\nconditions\nare\nin\na constant\nstate of flux and change, and\nnever static.\nThey can\u2019t even\nseem to invent new bromides to\nreplace\nthe\nwell-worn\ncliches\nused to express their unchang\ning, sacrosanct economic beliefs.\nBy nature optomistic.\nI too\nfeel that progress will be made in\nconquering current ills and that\nover the next 50 years or more\nthe world will move ahead. But\nI feel that many troubles lie in\nbetween and improvement won\u2019t\ncome easy does\nworthwhile\nconsiderable\never\neffort?\nanything\ncome without\nthink we can advance\nI\ndon't\nin any\nway by only boasting of our vir\ntues and smugly overlooking our\nills or\ncraveny avoiding\ndoing\nanything about them.\nListening to the crys against\ngovernment restrictions the 80th\ncongress removed price controls.\nAs was predicted, the resulting\nserious inflation brought a great\ner threat to the liberties of the\nmajority than\nthe\ncaused by the restrictions.\npresent\nbusiness\nannoyance\nrecession\nThe\nis\nprobably temporary, but I be\nlieve that without the huge gov\nernment purchases made neces\nsary by threats of another war\nthis recession could spiral into\nanother depression.\nMORE WOMEN\nCOOK ON\n.ai Cef\nTHAN ON\nANY OTHER RANGE\nDO YOU?\nIf not, you have a real treat in\nstore for you\u2014'cause cooking is\nfun, cooking is easy, cooking\nis delicious with a Magic Chef\ngas range. No wonder, \"More\nWomen Cook on Magic Chef\nThan On Any Other Range.\"\nSEE it UDAY AT\nTHE\nLAKE COUNTY\nGAS CO.\nCor. 3rd. and East St.\nFAIRPORT\nSpaulding Street\nWILLOUGHBY, OHIO\nTrue, Business is producing\nnew products, such as television,\nfor which there is great poten\ntial demand. But, speaking of\nrestriction,\nthe demand is re\nstricted by lack of purchasing\npower resulting\nfrom\ninflated\n.prices. And if credit restrictions\nwere removed, increased credit\nbuying would prolong prosperity\nbut increase the possibilities of\na serious bust. And another war\nwould destroy our economy as\nthe last one did Europe\u2019s.\nBusiness will boom as long as\nthere is a market\nand\na fair\nchance for profits; even less pro\nfits than those fat ones business\ntried to minimize over the past\ntwo years. Without a market bu\nsiness will curtail activities\u2014and\nprobably some will then blame\nthe curtailment on government\nrestrictions.\nOn the other side, some labor\npeople are ready to say that in\ndustrial recession is being deli\nberately promoted by industry to\npunish workers for voting De\nmocratic and to threaten con\ngress. That view is as unfair as\nit is absurd. As long as those\nholding different economic and\nPolitical\nview continue to\nal\nways suspect each other of hold\ning ulterior motives, it will be\nhard to achieve either industrial\npeace or the best possible type\nof legislation for our economic\nwell being.\nLabor,\ngovern\nbusiness,\nor\nment officials must never think\nthat only they are capable of be\ning honest in their convictions.\nThey must learn to examine the\nSTUDIO and CANDID\nPHOTOGRAPHS\nBabies and Children\na Specialty\nColeman Photo Service\n324 High St., Fairport\nviews of others, with an open\nmind, and put an end to name\ncalling and\nword\narguments.\nCrying socialism or reactionary\nat a proposed piece of legisla\ntion is easier than debating its\nmerits or evil, but it avoids the\nissue and is an injustice to the\nnation\u2019s welfare.\nRestricting\ncertain\nbusiness\npractises for the protection of\nthe majority is as necessary, de\nmocratic, and just as are certain\nrestriction\non\nmotorists.\nAnd\nyelling Sociaism only serves to\nmake Socialism look better than\nit is.\nLet us all examine our think\ning, try to eliminate an indis\ncriminate use of labels, and ex\npend greater efforts to find solu\ntions to our problems that will\nbe of most benefit to all, and\nnot just ourselves on the particu\nlar group we favor. Proud of our\nachievements\nbut\nrecognizing\nand working for the eradication\nof our faults, respecting and ex\namining different opinions on\nmethods of attaining the same\ncommon goal, we certainly can\nachieve a better and more pros\nperous tomorrow\u2014if we will. It\nis essentially a problem of re\nmoving the spiritual\nlag that\npresently looms large and dark\nbetween us and the bright new\nworld of the future.\nI don\u2019t want much on earth\nI\u2019m ready to admit it\nAnd if taxes and prices go much\nhigher\nI\u2019m sure I\u2019m not gonna git it.\nRed Ash\nSmokeless\nBig Lump\nCOAL\nBurns Like Pocahontas\nMYLLYKOSKI COAL\nPHONE 4225\nNELLBESS\n217 THIRD STREET\nFAIRPORT\nBLOOMFIELD\nDRESSES\n\u201cThe Dress of the Aristocrat\nat Budget Prices\u201d\n\u201814.95\nto\n\u201818.95\nTaffetas and Prints\nWOMEN\u2019S JEANS\nSizes 10 to 20_\n2.95\nSPECIAL SALE OF\nAprons\n59c\n80 Square Print Percale of Fresh,\nNew Spring Patterns","height":"20620","width":"14320"}}
